    <item>
      <title>Linting Helm Charts with Chart-Testing</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/2024-10-18-linting-helm-charts/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 18 Oct 2024 14:30:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/2024-10-18-linting-helm-charts/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        &lt;p&gt;When developing charts, it can be easy to make a mistake with YAML indentation or miss something out. Linting them should be considered a key part of your chart development and testing processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this post, I&amp;rsquo;m going to talk about the Helm &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/helm/chart-testing&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;chart-testing&lt;/a&gt; tool, but first lets look at the linter that&amp;rsquo;s included with the Helm client.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Helm Lint&lt;span class=&#34;hx-absolute -hx-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;helm-lint&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#helm-lint&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Helm client includes a linter. To use it, use the &lt;code&gt;lint&lt;/code&gt; command on a chart as a directory or a packaged archive. In the below example, I have a chart called &lt;code&gt;demo&lt;/code&gt; in a &lt;code&gt;charts&lt;/code&gt; directory:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx-relative hx-mt-6 first:hx-mt-0 hx-group/code&#34;&gt;
  

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;➜ helm lint charts/demo --strict
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;==&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt; Linting charts/demo
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;INFO&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; Chart.yaml: icon is recommended
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; chart&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;s&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; linted, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;0&lt;/span&gt; chart&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;s&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; failed&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx-opacity-0 hx-transition group-hover/code:hx-opacity-100 hx-flex hx-gap-1 hx-absolute hx-m-[11px] hx-right-0 hx-top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx-group/copybtn hx-transition-all active:hx-opacity-50 hx-bg-primary-700/5 hx-border hx-border-black/5 hx-text-gray-600 hover:hx-text-gray-900 hx-rounded-md hx-p-1.5 dark:hx-bg-primary-300/10 dark:hx-border-white/10 dark:hx-text-gray-400 dark:hover:hx-text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;copy-icon group-[.copied]/copybtn:hx-hidden hx-pointer-events-none hx-h-4 hx-w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;success-icon hx-hidden group-[.copied]/copybtn:hx-block hx-pointer-events-none hx-h-4 hx-w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

  
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s considered a good practice to use the &lt;code&gt;--strict&lt;/code&gt; flag to catch warnings during development and testing.
{: .prompt-tip }&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&amp;rsquo;ll see the above &lt;code&gt;INFO&lt;/code&gt; message when creating a default chart with &lt;code&gt;helm create&lt;/code&gt;. The missing icon won&amp;rsquo;t affect the operation of the chart, but it will affect the way it is displayed in UIs. You can use the &lt;code&gt;--quiet&lt;/code&gt; flag to print only warnings and errors if you prefer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let&amp;rsquo;s introduce an error so you can see the output. I&amp;rsquo;ve intentionally added an invalid key/value pair to the &lt;code&gt;values.yaml&lt;/code&gt; file:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx-relative hx-mt-6 first:hx-mt-0 hx-group/code&#34;&gt;
  

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;➜ helm lint charts/demo --quiet --strict
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;==&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt; Linting charts/demo
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;ERROR&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; values.yaml: unable to parse YAML: error converting YAML to JSON: yaml: line 48: did not find expected key
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;ERROR&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; templates/: cannot load values.yaml: error converting YAML to JSON: yaml: line 48: did not find expected key
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;ERROR&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; : unable to load chart
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;        cannot load values.yaml: error converting YAML to JSON: yaml: line 48: did not find expected key
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Error: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; chart&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;s&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; linted, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; chart&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;s&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; failed&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx-opacity-0 hx-transition group-hover/code:hx-opacity-100 hx-flex hx-gap-1 hx-absolute hx-m-[11px] hx-right-0 hx-top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx-group/copybtn hx-transition-all active:hx-opacity-50 hx-bg-primary-700/5 hx-border hx-border-black/5 hx-text-gray-600 hover:hx-text-gray-900 hx-rounded-md hx-p-1.5 dark:hx-bg-primary-300/10 dark:hx-border-white/10 dark:hx-text-gray-400 dark:hover:hx-text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;copy-icon group-[.copied]/copybtn:hx-hidden hx-pointer-events-none hx-h-4 hx-w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;success-icon hx-hidden group-[.copied]/copybtn:hx-block hx-pointer-events-none hx-h-4 hx-w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

  
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Errors will return a non-zero exit code and fail the pipeline.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Feedback Levels&lt;span class=&#34;hx-absolute -hx-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;feedback-levels&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#feedback-levels&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Helm provides 3 levels of actionable feedback about charts. These are useful to know in case you come across them:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;INFO&lt;/code&gt; - Charts can be installed (exit code 0)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;ERROR&lt;/code&gt; - Linter encounters things that will cause the chart to fail installation (non-zero exit code)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;WARNING&lt;/code&gt; - Encounters issues that break with convention or recommendation (exit code 0 by default, but can be set to non-zero with the &lt;code&gt;--strict&lt;/code&gt; flag)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Kubernetes API Version Checks&lt;span class=&#34;hx-absolute -hx-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;kubernetes-api-version-checks&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#kubernetes-api-version-checks&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Helm version &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/helm/helm/releases/tag/v3.14.0&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;v3.14.0&lt;/a&gt; introduced a &lt;code&gt;--kube-version&lt;/code&gt; flag for capabilities and deprecation checks. This already exists in the &lt;code&gt;helm template&lt;/code&gt; command. If you&amp;rsquo;re using a tool like &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/FairwindsOps/pluto&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;pluto&lt;/a&gt;, you can now replace it with this instead:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx-relative hx-mt-6 first:hx-mt-0 hx-group/code&#34;&gt;
  

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;helm lint charts/demo --strict --kube-version 1.31&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx-opacity-0 hx-transition group-hover/code:hx-opacity-100 hx-flex hx-gap-1 hx-absolute hx-m-[11px] hx-right-0 hx-top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx-group/copybtn hx-transition-all active:hx-opacity-50 hx-bg-primary-700/5 hx-border hx-border-black/5 hx-text-gray-600 hover:hx-text-gray-900 hx-rounded-md hx-p-1.5 dark:hx-bg-primary-300/10 dark:hx-border-white/10 dark:hx-text-gray-400 dark:hover:hx-text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;copy-icon group-[.copied]/copybtn:hx-hidden hx-pointer-events-none hx-h-4 hx-w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;success-icon hx-hidden group-[.copied]/copybtn:hx-block hx-pointer-events-none hx-h-4 hx-w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

  
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please be aware of the &lt;a href=&#34;https://helm.sh/docs/topics/version_skew/#supported-version-skew&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;supported version skew policy&lt;/a&gt; between Helm and Kubernetes versions if you&amp;rsquo;re wondering why it&amp;rsquo;s not working as intended.
{: .prompt-warning }&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That&amp;rsquo;s about as far as you can go with the &lt;code&gt;helm lint&lt;/code&gt; command. Now let&amp;rsquo;s turn our attention to the chart-testing tool, &lt;code&gt;ct&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Chart-Testing&lt;span class=&#34;hx-absolute -hx-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;chart-testing&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#chart-testing&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Helm &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/helm/chart-testing&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;chart-testing&lt;/a&gt; tool (&lt;code&gt;ct&lt;/code&gt;) provides more advanced testing capabilities, and is meant to be used for linting and testing pull requests. It automatically detects charts changed against the target branch (&lt;code&gt;main&lt;/code&gt; in this example).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Lint Command&lt;span class=&#34;hx-absolute -hx-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;lint-command&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#lint-command&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you look at the &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/helm/chart-testing/blob/main/doc/ct_lint.md&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;ct lint&lt;/a&gt; command, you&amp;rsquo;ll see a lot of options to use. The defaults are sufficient to get started.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Check Version Increment&lt;span class=&#34;hx-absolute -hx-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;check-version-increment&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#check-version-increment&#34; class=&#34;subheading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Permalink for this section&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;I really like the &lt;code&gt;--check-version-increment&lt;/code&gt; option. This activates a check for chart version increments, and is useful if you version your chart separate from your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here&amp;rsquo;s an example of what you&amp;rsquo;ll see if you make a change to a chart without bumping the version:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx-relative hx-mt-6 first:hx-mt-0 hx-group/code&#34;&gt;
  

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-yaml&#34; data-lang=&#34;yaml&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;Run ct lint --target-branch main&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;Linting charts...&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;Charts to be processed&lt;/span&gt;:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;demo =&amp;gt; (version&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;0.1.0&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;, path&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;charts/demo&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;Linting chart &amp;#34;demo =&amp;gt; (version: \&amp;#34;0.1.0\&amp;#34;, path: \&amp;#34;charts/demo\&amp;#34;)&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;Checking chart &amp;#34;demo =&amp;gt; (version: \&amp;#34;0.1.0\&amp;#34;, path: \&amp;#34;charts/demo\&amp;#34;)&amp;#34; for a version bump...&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;Old chart version&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;0.1.0&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;New chart version&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;0.1.0&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;Error: failed linting charts&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;failed processing charts&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;✖︎ demo =&amp;gt; (version&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;0.1.0&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;, path&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;charts/demo&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;) &amp;gt; chart version not ok. Needs a version bump!&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;failed linting charts&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;failed processing charts&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;Error&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;Process completed with exit code 1.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx-opacity-0 hx-transition group-hover/code:hx-opacity-100 hx-flex hx-gap-1 hx-absolute hx-m-[11px] hx-right-0 hx-top-0&#34;&gt;
  &lt;button
    class=&#34;hextra-code-copy-btn hx-group/copybtn hx-transition-all active:hx-opacity-50 hx-bg-primary-700/5 hx-border hx-border-black/5 hx-text-gray-600 hover:hx-text-gray-900 hx-rounded-md hx-p-1.5 dark:hx-bg-primary-300/10 dark:hx-border-white/10 dark:hx-text-gray-400 dark:hover:hx-text-gray-50&#34;
    title=&#34;Copy code&#34;
  &gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;copy-icon group-[.copied]/copybtn:hx-hidden hx-pointer-events-none hx-h-4 hx-w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;success-icon hx-hidden group-[.copied]/copybtn:hx-block hx-pointer-events-none hx-h-4 hx-w-4&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

  
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bump the version, then try again:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;hextra-code-block hx-relative hx-mt-6 first:hx-mt-0 hx-group/code&#34;&gt;
  

&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-yaml&#34; data-lang=&#34;yaml&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;Run ct lint --target-branch main&lt;/span&gt;
